Anglicized. Or Anglicised. Donna Inez is don Juan’s mother in the Lord Byron poem, in which he pronounces the name of the fictional ladies’ man with an English J and rhymes it with “you on.”  In the original Spanish play by Tirso de Molina, doña Inés is his intended. 

Byron’s poem came about 200 years later.

